description: From Old French empreinte, from the past participle of empreindre, from Latin imprimere.

entries.meaning: An impression; the mark left behind by printing something.
examples: The day left an imprint in my mind.

entries.meaning: The name and details of a publisher or printer, as printed in a book etc.; a publishing house.
A distinctive marking, symbol or logo.
examples: The shirts bore the company imprint on the right sleeve.

description: From Middle English emprinten, enprinten, from Old French empreinter, from the past participle of empreindre, from Latin imprimere.

verbs.description: imprint (third-person singular simple present imprints, present participle imprinting, simple past and past participle imprinted)

entries.meaning: To leave a print, impression, image, etc.
examples: For a fee, they can imprint the envelopes with a monogram.

entries.meaning: To learn something indelibly at a particular stage of life, such as who one's parents are.
To mark a gene as being from a particular parent so that only one of the two copies of the gene is expressed.
